# Ignore vendored scripts in GitHub stats
src/static/scripts/* linguist-vendored

# binarybeachio: shell scripts and Jinja templates that get executed
# (or sed'd into) inside the Linux container build MUST stay LF-terminated,
# regardless of the cloning host's core.autocrlf setting. Without this, a
# Windows clone with core.autocrlf=true converts these to CRLF, the shebang
# on shell scripts becomes `#!/bin/sh\r` (invalid path), and the container
# crashloops with `exec /start.sh: no such file or directory`. Burned
# 2026-04-30 on first deploy of bb-vaultwarden-fork.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.j2 text eol=lf
Dockerfile* text eol=lf
